{"title": "Hesitant Sacrifice", "content": "When a hero is forced to make the ultimate sacrifice for the greater good and they have a sudden realisation: \"Wait, I Don't Want To Die!\" It might be a Chosen One wondering why they specifically have to die instead of somebody else (though of course, if everyone has to die, that doesn't necessarily make the deal any sweeter, and might even make an individual death seem even more pointless).\n\nIf our hero takes the \"blustering\" route, expect wild rationalizations, such as \"I've already done enough!\" or \"I'm too young to die!\" (even if the hero is, in fact, very old). \"I have a wife and kids!\" or \"This can't happen to me! I'm a [self-important description of oneself]!\" may be heard in more comedic works.\n\nThis scenario is often used to show a somewhat flawed, human side to the hero, and also to make the scene more dramatic. It is characterized by very unheroic responses and actions wherein they lose bravery, resolve, consideration of the greater good and, sometimes, dignity. It is likely that the hero will need someone to help them calm down if they don't end up doing so themselves and Face Death with Dignity. There's also the possibility that this will be their Despair Event Horizon and might lead them to try and Screw Destiny by running away. The hero may also realize that there's something or someone that needed their help and he needs himself to be alive to do so, which makes the sacrifice problematic. Attempts to Take a Third Option don't usually work out. Although there is the possibility of a Deus ex Machina to save the day, this may or may not affect the impact of the scene.\n\nThere is also the chance that, if not done right, it could make the hero look like a Dirty Coward in an unsympathetic way.\n\nUnlike a Heroic BSoD or Heroic Safe Mode, this realization is very emotional and often met with the Five Stages of Grief.\n\nSee also Mortality Phobia for the fear of death in general and Mid-Suicide Regret for hesitance during a suicide attempt.\n\nSince this is a Death Trope, there will be spoilers. Read at your own risk.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HesitantSacrifice", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/NieR", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/InuYasha", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/BusouRenkin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Trigun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Bleach", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/NadiaTheSecretOfBlueWater", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/EndOfEvangelion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AttackOnTitan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Hellsing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TokyoGhoul", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/PandoraHearts", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/YuGiOh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/MarvelStarWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Runaways", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Fables", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/PeterPan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BurtReynolds", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DomDeLuise", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/PaulWilliams", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TwoHands", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AngelsWithDirtyFaces", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/IngmarBergman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheSeventhSeal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Help", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/WonderWoman2017", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotterAndTheDeathlyHallows", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheSagaOfDarrenShan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TwentyFour", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BlackAdder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheHauntingHour", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekVoyager", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Queen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/HollywoodUndead", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Vocaloid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBible", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/JesusChristSuperstar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TalesOfTheAbyss", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StreetFighter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Vid